<article doi="10.15252/embj.2019101744"><fig id="27946"><title>: Crystal structure of Sir4 H‑BRCT A) Domain architecture of Sir4.</title><label>Figure 1</label><graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?figure_id=27946"/><sd-panel panel_id="75500">Domain architecture of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag704403496sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag>. <sd-pretag id="sdPretag387936558sd" category="assay">Crystal structures</sd-pretag> have been determined for the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag673179024sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1215819103sd" type="geneprod" role="component">Ku80</sd-pretag>-<sd-pretag id="sdPretag247873441sd" parent-tag-id="2">binding</sd-pretag> motif (KBM) in complex with <sd-pretag id="sdPretag853965312sd" type="geneprod" role="component">Ku80</sd-pretag>, the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1631338450sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag>-<sd-pretag id="sdPretag1256591882sd" parent-tag-id="3">interacting</sd-pretag> domain (SID) in complex with <sd-pretag id="sdPretag128869198sd" type="geneprod" role="component">Sir2</sd-pretag>, and the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1794162597sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> self-dimerization coiled-coil module (CC) (PDB 5Y59, 4IAO, and 1NYH, respectively). <sd-pretag id="sdPretag426433264sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT (orange box, this work) locates to the first half of the partitioning and anchoring domain (PAD) which recruits silenced chromatin to the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1691161300sd" type="subcellular" role="component">nuclear envelope</sd-pretag>. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=75500"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="75501">ClustalO (Sievers et al, 2011) multiple <sd-pretag id="sdPretag211101568sd" category="assay">sequence alignment</sd-pretag> of various <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2010057413sd" type="organism" role="component">yeast</sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag761601773sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag74460083sd" type="molecule" role="component">proteins</sd-pretag> focusing on the putative new structural domain and comparison with <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1264545301sd" type="organism" role="component"><em>S. cerevisiae</em></sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag569646208sd" parent-tag-id="100">Dbf4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT. <sd-pretag id="sdPretag347482690sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag757988669sd" category="assay">sequences</sd-pretag>: ScSir4 (<sd-pretag id="sdPretag407918159sd" type="organism" role="component"><em>Saccharomyces cerevisiae</em></sd-pretag>, Uniprot P11978), NdSir4 (<em>Naumovozyma dairenensis</em>, G0W8P4), NcSir4 (<em>Naumovozyma castellii</em>, G0VBN1), KnSir4 (<em>Kazachstania naganishii</em>, J7S2D5), KaSir4 (<em>Kazachstania africana</em>, H2AVL7). <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=75501"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="75502">Scheme of the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag406589390sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1151613127sd" category="assay">crystal structure</sd-pretag> in two orientations rotated by ~<sd-pretag id="sdPretag1484577197sd" category="time">120</sd-pretag> ° around a vertical axis. Colors gradually vary from blue (N-terminus) to red (C-terminus) while the surface is shown in grey (transparent). Termini and secondary structural elements are labelled. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=75502"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="75503">Superposition of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1323691915sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT (orange) onto the H‑BRCT domain of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag453207668sd" parent-tag-id="100">Dbf4</sd-pretag> (PDB 3QBZ, cyan) in two orientations as in (C). Secondary structural elements, termini and the elongated <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1930075617sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> loop connecting helix <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2014489995sd" type="geneprod" role="component">α3</sd-pretag> and strand β4 are labelled. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=75503"/></sd-panel></fig><fig id="27947"><title>: Sir4 H‑BRCT structural comparison with Dbf4 H‑BRCT and Rad53 FHA1 binding A) Structure-based sequence alignment between H‑BRCT domains of Sir4 (top) and Dbf4 (PDB 3QBZ, bottom).</title><label>Figure 2</label><graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?figure_id=27947"/><sd-panel panel_id="75504">Structure-<sd-pretag id="sdPretag544058038sd" type="molecule" role="component">based</sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag968800956sd" category="assay">sequence alignment</sd-pretag> between H‑BRCT domains of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1777003910sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> (top) and <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1839974950sd" parent-tag-id="100">Dbf4</sd-pretag> (PDB 3QBZ, bottom). Secondary structural elements present in the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2088602532sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1724349704sd" category="assay">crystal structure</sd-pretag> are displayed above the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1550067209sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1806750799sd" category="assay">sequence</sd-pretag> (α, α-helix; β, β-strand; η, 3.10 helix). <sd-pretag id="sdPretag92477909sd" parent-tag-id="100">Dbf4</sd-pretag> residues strongly contributing to <sd-pretag id="sdPretag555081227sd" type="geneprod" role="component">Rad53</sd-pretag> FHA1 <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1485160861sd" parent-tag-id="2">binding</sd-pretag> are highlighted with <sd-pretag id="sdPretag895352770sd" type="geneprod" role="component">black</sd-pretag> (interface I) and blue (interface II) asterisks. The elongated loop connecting helix <sd-pretag id="sdPretag767956455sd" type="geneprod" role="component">α3</sd-pretag> and strand β4 in <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1237651412sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT is labelled with an orange bar and the Tyr198 (<sd-pretag id="sdPretag1335180043sd" parent-tag-id="100">Dbf4</sd-pretag>) to Lys1064 (<sd-pretag id="sdPretag539069132sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag>) exchange is highlighted with colored arrows. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=75504"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="75505">Superposition of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1127586330sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT (orange) onto the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1405837720sd" parent-tag-id="100">Dbf4</sd-pretag>-<sd-pretag id="sdPretag1511536435sd" type="geneprod" role="component">Rad53</sd-pretag>-CDC7 complex (cyan, grey, blue) (PDB 5T2S) in two orientations rotated by ~180° around a vertical axis. Helices are displayed as barrels and <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2024741410sd" type="molecule" role="component">protein</sd-pretag>-<sd-pretag id="sdPretag475459263sd" type="molecule" role="component">protein</sd-pretag> interfaces between <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1496358081sd" parent-tag-id="100">Dbf4</sd-pretag> and FHA1 of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag906386584sd" type="geneprod" role="component">Rad53</sd-pretag> are highlighted with dashed circles in <sd-pretag id="sdPretag439197006sd" type="geneprod" role="component">black</sd-pretag> (interface I) and blue (interface II). <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=75505"/></sd-panel></fig><fig id="27949"><title>: Structural basis of Sir4 H‑BRCT interaction with phospho-peptides A) The electrostatic surface potential covering a range from -4 kT/e (red/acidic) to +4 kT/e (blue/basic) is mapped onto the Sir4 H‑BRCT structure to highlight the basic patch on the H‑BRCT surface.</title><label>Figure 3</label><graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?figure_id=27949"/><sd-panel panel_id="75506">The electrostatic surface potential covering a range from -4 kT/e (red/acidic) to +4 kT/e (blue/basic) is mapped onto the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag710647985sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT structure to highlight the basic patch on the H‑BRCT surface. <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1078452576sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT is shown in two orientations rotated by 180° and selected residues are labeled. Superpositions of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1835148726sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT-Esc1<sup>pS1450</sup> (grey cartoon, <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1135059400sd" type="molecule" role="component">peptide</sd-pretag> as sticks in atom colors), <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1079276031sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT-Ty5<sup>pS1095</sup> (blue cartoon, <sd-pretag id="sdPretag227763134sd" type="molecule" role="component">peptide</sd-pretag> as sticks in atom colors), and <sd-pretag id="sdPretag856372837sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT-Ubp10<sup>pT123</sup> (green cartoon, <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2076045221sd" type="molecule" role="component">peptide</sd-pretag> as sticks in atom colors) <sd-pretag id="sdPretag527104963sd" type="molecule" role="component">peptide</sd-pretag> complex structures reveal the highly similar conformation of <sd-pretag id="sdPretag959501160sd" type="molecule" role="component">peptide</sd-pretag> binders. Esc1<sup>pS1450</sup>, Ty5<sup>pS1095</sup>, and Ubp10<sup>pT123</sup> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1670745056sd" type="molecule" role="component">peptides</sd-pretag> used for co-crystallization are indicated with residues <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1283059210sd" category="assay">modeled</sd-pretag> in the structures in bold and residues that contribute most <sd-pretag id="sdPretag770955431sd" parent-tag-id="2">binding</sd-pretag> to <sd-pretag id="sdPretag256307335sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT boxed. <graphic href="https://api.sourcedata.io/file.php?panel_id=75506"/></sd-panel><sd-panel panel_id="75507">Detailed view of the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag496712503sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT-Esc1<sup>pS1450</sup> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag2016632957sd" type="molecule" role="component">peptide</sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1193655951sd" parent-tag-id="3">interaction</sd-pretag>. <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1879573498sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT is displayed as orange <sd-pretag id="sdPretag230039618sd" category="assay">model</sd-pretag> with residues involved in <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1704068954sd" type="molecule" role="component">peptide</sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1122436960sd" parent-tag-id="2">binding</sd-pretag> shown as sticks (orange, atom colors). The Esc1<sup>pS1450</sup> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag956510879sd" type="molecule" role="component">peptide</sd-pretag> is presented as sticks in grey (atom colors). Electrostatic <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1731640384sd" parent-tag-id="3">interactions</sd-pretag> are highlighted with green dotted lines while main hydrophobic contacts are shown as dotted lines in <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1443640632sd" type="geneprod" role="component">black</sd-pretag>. Detailed view of the <sd-pretag id="sdPretag502479250sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H‑BRCT-Ty5<sup>pS1095</sup> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag185073009sd" type="molecule" role="component">peptide</sd-pretag> <sd-pretag id="sdPretag1474306191sd" parent-tag-id="3">interaction</sd-pretag>. <sd-pretag id="sdPretag64132544sd" parent-gene-tag-id="4" parent-protein-tag-id="16">Sir4</sd-pretag> H